<section id="what-are-cookies" class="padded-section">
  <div class="max-width">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>
        <span class="highlight-container">What are cookies?</span>
      </h2>
    </div>
    <div class="section-content">
      <p>Cookies are small data files that are placed on your computer or mobile device when you visit a website. Cookies are widely used by website owners in order to make their websites work, or to work more efficiently, as well as to provide reporting information.</p>
      <p>Cookies set by the website owner (in this case, us) are called “first party cookies". Cookies set by parties other than the website owner are called "third party cookies". Third party cookies enable third party features or functionality to be provided on or through the website (e.g. advertising, interactive content, and analytics). The parties that set these third party cookies can recognize your computer both when it visits the website in question and also when it visits certain other websites.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="how-we-use" class="padded-section">
  <div class="max-width">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>
        <span class="highlight-container">How do we use cookies and similar technologies?</span>
      </h2>
    </div>
    <div class="section-content">
      <div class="subsection">
        <p>As advocates for digital privacy, we're happy to report that we don't use cookies on our website (terrabyte.eco). By carefully planning and implementing our site functionality and service partners, you should not find any first party or third party cookies on our site.</p>
        <p>With that being said - we <em>do</em> use browser-based storage technologies such as LocalStorage and SessionStorage to enhance user experience (e.g. site preferences, dismissing banners). These technologies store data locally on your device and do not transmit to our servers.</p>

        <p>Other pages we manage that link to this Privacy Policy use similar web technologies, but may also incorporate third-party cookies. These exceptions include the Pinekeepers website (pinekeepers.com), the Wasted Space website (wastedspace.fun), the Pixel Planet Today website (pixelplanettoday.com), the Pixel Planet Today blog (blog.pixelplanettoday.com), and the Pixel Planet Today webstore (shop.pixelplanettoday.com or pixelplanettoday.square.site).</p>

        <ul class="no-bullets">
          <li><h3>Pinekeepers (<a class="text-link" href="https://pinekeepers.com" target="_blank">https://pinekeepers.com</a>)</h3></li>
          <li>
            <ul class="no-bullets">
              <li><p>The Pinekeepers website, while small, only uses cookies when users interact with the video player. This is due to an embedded Youtube video. Once the user has selected to play the video, the video player may leave cookies on your device to track user sign in, play count, and other analytics. You can access the full Youtube Privacy Policy <a class="text-link" href="https://policies.google.com/privacy?hl=en" target="_blank">here</a>.</p></li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li><h3>Wasted Space (<a class="text-link" href="https://wastedspace.fun" target="_blank">https://wastedspace.fun</a>)</h3></li>
          <li>
            <ul class="no-bullets">
              <li><p>As of posting this Cookie Policy, the Wasted Space website does not leverage cookies or similar technologies.</p></li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li><h3>Pixel Planet Today: Website (<a class="text-link" href="https://pixelplanettoday.com" target="_blank">https://pixelplanettoday.com</a>)</h3></li>
          <li>
            <ul class="no-bullets">
              <li><p>As of posting this Cookie Policy, the Pixel Planet Today website no longer incorporates a newsletter signup form provided by Hubspot. However these cookies could still exist on your machine if you have not cleared cookies. You can view the full Hubspot Privacy Policy <a class="text-link" href="https://legal.hubspot.com/privacy-policy?_ga=2.146363760.593754624.1663428374-35416247.1663428374" target="_blank">here</a>.</p></li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li><h3>Pixel Planet Today: Blog (<a class="text-link" href="https://blog.pixelplanettoday.com" target="_blank">https://blog.pixelplanettoday.com</a>)</h3></li>
          <li>
            <ul class="no-bullets">
              <li><p>The Pixel Planet Today blog is built using WordPress and WordPress plugins. We have elected to use WordPress plugins that do not rely on storing information to the users device, but WordPress itself relies on them in some circumstances. You can view the full WordPress Privacy Policy <a class="text-link" href="https://wordpress.org/about/privacy/" target="_blank">here</a>.</p></li>
            </ul>
          </li>

          <li><h3>Pixel Planet Today: Webstore (<a class="text-link" href="https://shop.pixelplanettoday.com" target="_blank">https://shop.pixelplanettoday.com</a> or <a class="text-link" href="https://pixelplanettoday.square.site" target="_blank">pixelplanettoday.square.site</a>)</h3></li>
          <li>
            <ul class="no-bullets">
              <li><p>The Pixel Planet Today Webstore is hosted and created through Square, a E-commerce platform used by small businesses. Due to the nature of customers adding items to a virtual cart, going through a checkout process, and entering personal information, Square uses cookies to keep user information secure, and not lose track of your order. If you'd like to learn more, you can access the full Square Privacy Notice <a class="text-link" href="https://squareup.com/us/en/legal/general/privacy" target="_blank">here</a>.</p></li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>In addition to the information listed above, we may collect information about you in order to provide products, services, and other features to you or other users. To read more on what information we may process, read our <a class="text-link" href="./privacy-policy.html">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="subsection">
        <p><b>Please Note:</b> If you are using a browser like Google Chrome or Microsoft Edge that allows you to 'Sign In', those third party cookies may still display while you visit our site. This is a cookie we can neither block or account for as this is a cookie that is dependent on user software choices.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="how-to-control" class="padded-section">
  <div class="max-width">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>
        <span class="highlight-container">How can I control cookies?</span>
      </h2>
    </div>
    <div class="section-content">
      <div class="subsection">
        <p>While we limit the amount of cookies used on our site(s), other websites use more - meaning the cookies you're storing could add up. By using your browser's settings, you may be able to limit or block websites from storing cookies on your device where applicable. In many cases, selecting to delete cookies from your browser will also delete other data, such as Local Storage (as mentioned above).</p>
        <p>In addition, most advertising networks offer you a way to opt out of targeted advertising. If you would like to find out more information, please visit <a class="text-link" href="http:/www.aboutads.info/choices/" target="_blank">http:/www.aboutads.info/choices/</a> or <a class="text-link" href="http://www.youronlinechoices.com" target="_blank">http://www.youronlinechoices.com</a>.</p>
        <p>Please note: Clearing cookies from your browser may also delete data stored via LocalStorage or SessionStorage, which could reset site preferences or dismissals.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

